{
 "name": "RPlog_Good_Morning_Myrkr",
 "title": "Good Morning, Myrkr",
 "summary": "In the residents' barracks at Talon Karrde's base on Myrkr, the Jedi Master Jessalyn finds her student, the master mechanic Orson, asleep amid his gadgets after a long night, and rouses him for breakfast. She discovers him designing lightsaber casings -- some modeled on her own saber -- and the two fall into a long, searching conversation about what it truly means to be a Jedi. Jessalyn confides her growing fear that she has lost control and lost touch with her own purpose, while Orson, shaped by a hard life, counsels her to be careful, not to rush, and reminds her of the friendship, comfort, and love worth fighting for. Their talk turns tender as they lean their foreheads together, mixing mentorship with deepening affection, and drifts into the technical artistry of Orson's ambitious dual-phase lightsaber design. The morning becomes a quiet, intimate exchange of doubt, encouragement, and craft between teacher and apprentice.",
 "rows": [
